I am sincerely glad that I have all of you and am able to treat you all pretty decently. It is a pleasure that I feel pretty steadily now, though sometimes when I'm off feed or perhaps more than ordinarily sick of "litrachoor" I can't see so well. But I am, deep down, delighted to be able to do this and to have you all to do it for. 
Mrs. B. is certainly a fine person. We want to do something for her Christmas, and Mona and I think we know what would probably give her pleasure. 
Mama, I am wondering if it would not be better for you and all ofus if you would consent to come up here for your birthday and stay only as long as you want to. You could take in some good shows, and you could go back when you felt that way. It would be more crowded for you here, of course, but wouldn't it be all right for a few weeks? Our time there would be so short and the trip so strenuous. We'd not get used to being there at all, and winter is no time anyway. Don't you want to have a change and go to some symphony concerts, recitals and shows? I think that would be fine, and Mona favors it very much. We are more than ordinarily happy here now, and you would be too, I think. 
Endless love,
Jno. 